div.p:
Meanwhile there were six tīrthika teachers living in Rājagṛha who entertained the conceit of omniscience although they were
                            not omniscient: Pūraṇa Kāśyapa;  Gośālīputra, the wandering mendicant; Sañjayin, son of Vairaṭṭī;
                            Ajita of the hair shawl; Kakuda, a descendant of Kātyāyana; and Jñātiputra, the Nirgrantha.
